/*
 data types are of two type primitive and non-primitive.
 Non-primitive-> String,arrays,class,structure,etc.
 primitive -> boolean and numeric
 numeric-> Character and Integral
 Integral->Integer and floating point
 Boolean-> boolean
 Character->char
 Integer->byte,short,int,long
 Floating Point->float,double
 primitive->byte,short,int,long,float,double,char,boolean

 1byte = 8bits;
 char(size)->2byte; default value 0(blank space)
 short(size)->2byte;default value 0
 int(size)->4byte;default value 0
 long(size)->8byte;default value 0
 float(size)->4byte;default value 0.0
 double(size)->8byte;default value 0.0
 boolean(size)->1bit(but proper size decided at run time,jvm will decide) default false

 size of primitive data type is fixed
 non primitive size will be allocated at run time as you specified




 */
